## Architecture & Data Flow
- NextJS Frontend (App Router) renders the UI, handles routing/search, and fetches content via HTTP requests to Strapi.
- StrapiCMS Backend (Node.js) exposes REST endpoints, applies auth/validation, and persists structured content in the configured SQL database (SQLite by default, Postgres/MySQL optional per `.env`).
- Media uploads and generated assets are served directly by Strapi through its `/uploads` pipeline, keeping the frontend stateless.

